parameters.name: AccessIp
parameters.description: The backend IP address to be modified in FULLNAT address translation.

parameters.name: AccessPort
parameters.description: The backend port to be modified in FULLNAT port mapping. Valid values: **1** to **65535**.

parameters.name: ClientToken
parameters.description:
The client token that is used to ensure the idempotence of the request.

You can use the client to generate the token, but you must make sure that the token is unique among different requests. The token can contain only ASCII characters.

>  If you do not specify this parameter, the system automatically uses the **request ID** as the **client token**. The **request ID** may be different for each request.

parameters.name: DryRun
parameters.description:
Specifies whether to perform only a dry run, without performing the actual request. Valid values:

*   **true**: performs only a dry run. The system checks the request for potential issues, including missing parameter values, incorrect request syntax, and service limits. If the request fails the dry run, an error message is returned. If the request passes the dry run, the `DryRunOperation` error code is returned.
*   **false**: performs a dry run and performs the actual request. If the request passes the dry run, a 2xx HTTP status code is returned and the operation is performed.

parameters.name: FullNatEntryDescription
parameters.description:
The new description of the FULLNAT entry.

You can leave this parameter empty or enter a description. If you enter a description, the description must be 2 to 256 characters in length and cannot start with `http://` or `https://`.

parameters.name: FullNatEntryId
parameters.description: The ID of the FULLNAT entry to be modified.

parameters.name: FullNatEntryName
parameters.description:
The new name of the FULLNAT entry.

The name must be 2 to 128 characters in length. It must start with a letter but cannot start with `http://` or `https://`.

parameters.name: FullNatTableId
parameters.description: The ID of the FULLNAT table to be modified.

parameters.name: IpProtocol
parameters.description:
The protocol of the packets that are forwarded by the port. Valid values:

*   **TCP**: TCP
*   **UDP**

parameters.name: NatIp
parameters.description: The NAT IP address to be modified.

parameters.name: NatIpPort
parameters.description: The frontend port to be modified in FULLNAT port mapping. Valid values: **1** to **65535**.

parameters.name: NetworkInterfaceId
parameters.description: The ID of the elastic network interface (ENI) to be modified.

parameters.name: RegionId
parameters.description:
The region ID of the Virtual Private Cloud (VPC) NAT gateway to which the FULLNAT entry to be modified belongs.

You can call the [DescribeRegions](~~36063~~) operation to query the most recent region list.
